From: chat-template-patches
Subject: [G1] Replace `is sequence` with a portable iterable check (minijinja)

Targets: templates/gemma4/upstream/<size>.jinja — Google's 2026-07-09
template. Applies to all five sizes (12B-it, 26B-A4B-it, 31B-it, E2B-it,
E4B-it); the affected lines are identical across them.

Status: OPT-IN. Required for minijinja-based runtimes (LM Studio's MCP
path). Standard `jinja2` implements the `sequence` test, so this patch is a
no-op there for normal inputs.

Failure mode: LM Studio's minijinja does not implement the `sequence` test:

    Error rendering prompt with jinja template: "Unknown test: sequence"

Every Gemma 4 MCP tool call fails. Google's 2026-07-09 rewrite did not
address this and in fact GREW the surface from 3 sites to 4 — it added
`tool_body is sequence` in the new multimodal tool-response branch.

Fix: replace all four `is sequence` tests with the portable form
`X is iterable and X is not string and X is not mapping`:

  - `format_argument`            (argument)
  - first-system-message handler (messages[0]['content'])
  - tool-response body           (tool_body — already had `is not string`)
  - assistant/user content parts (message.get('content'))

Verified byte-identical under jinja2 across all Gemma 4 fixtures x
{no kwargs, tools, preserve_thinking, enable_thinking} (12 render combos).

Bonus correctness fix (a real behaviour change, deliberate): jinja2's
`sequence` test returns true for MAPPINGS, so a dict-valued `content`
previously entered the content-parts loop, iterated the dict's string keys,
and raised `'str object' has no attribute 'get'`. The explicit
`is not mapping` guard excludes that case, so the turn renders instead of
crashing. This is the only input class where the patched and stock
templates differ under jinja2.

Prior art: u/Reaper_9382, r/LocalLLaMA "Fix Gemma 4 MCP tool calls broken in
LM Studio" (Apr 2026). Patch first shipped 2026-07-20 (previously
catalog-only) — Google's expansion of the surface made it worth shipping.

--- a/templates/gemma4/upstream/26B-A4B-it.jinja
+++ b/templates/gemma4/upstream/26B-A4B-it.jinja
@@ -142,7 +142,7 @@
             :{{- format_argument(value, escape_keys=escape_keys) -}}
         {%- endfor -%}
         {{- '}' -}}
-    {%- elif argument is sequence -%}
+    {%- elif argument is iterable and argument is not string and argument is not mapping -%}
         {{- '[' -}}
         {%- for item in argument -%}
             {{- format_argument(item, escape_keys=escape_keys) -}}
@@ -197,7 +197,7 @@
     {%- if messages and messages[0]['role'] in ['system', 'developer'] -%}
         {%- if messages[0]['content'] is string -%}
             {{- messages[0]['content'] | trim -}}
-        {%- elif messages[0]['content'] is sequence -%}
+        {%- elif messages[0]['content'] is iterable and messages[0]['content'] is not string and messages[0]['content'] is not mapping -%}
             {%- for item in messages[0]['content'] -%}
                 {{- item['text'] | trim + ' '-}}
             {%- endfor -%}
@@ -294,7 +294,7 @@
                         {%- set tool_body = follow.get('content') -%}
                         {%- if tool_body is string -%}
                             {{- format_tool_response_block(ns_tname.name, tool_body) -}}
-                        {%- elif tool_body is sequence and tool_body is not string -%}
+                        {%- elif tool_body is iterable and tool_body is not string and tool_body is not mapping -%}
                             {%- set ns_txt = namespace(s='') -%}
                             {%- for part in tool_body -%}
                                 {%- if part.get('type') == 'text' -%}
@@ -327,7 +327,7 @@
                 {%- else -%}
                     {{- message['content'] | trim -}}
                 {%- endif -%}
-            {%- elif message.get('content') is sequence -%}
+            {%- elif message.get('content') is iterable and message.get('content') is not string and message.get('content') is not mapping -%}
                 {%- for item in message['content'] -%}
                     {%- if item.get('type') == 'text' -%}
                         {%- if role == 'model' -%}
